  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "Wouldn't it be feasible to make it as easy as possible, to digitally sign AND confirm digital signatures of a developer or security auditor on any given deployed contract? Such as requesting a \"signature verification\" from the contract itself via CLI or Mist? Maybe a specific storage instance per contract, reserved for digital signatures? \n\nAuditing of smart contracts will surely become the norm within the next few years, since storage of value often occurs within a contract, as well as any reliance on general data integrity (for public chains especially). The easier it is to verify a CERTAIN TRUSTED PARTY's private key signed a specific contract, along with the usual bytecode verification, the more businesses and organizations may be willing trust the Ethereum platform if / when it makes it's way into a mainstream environment in the future.\n",
