    "body": "This is indeed very easy to do on Ethereum.\n\nSince every transaction is itself signed by a public key, all you actually need is a simple registry contract where anyone can approve an address, along with any other meta-data you think is relevant, maybe a final security rating, for example.\n\nAll that remains after a simple registry contract like that is the user experience, for how to represent a contract that may have been reviewed by dozens if not hundreds or thousands of peers?\n\nMaybe incorporating bonding into the review process?  Lots of fun possibilities.\n",
