    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "@flyswatter Interesting insights. If Ethereum contracts could be signed securely like application binaries on a PC, and display a warning dialog if not trusted or signed (via CLI or Mist GUI) before executing them, I think end-user trust levels may be more in line with mainstream use. \n\nAdditionally, a \"Trust this source\" feature could be added to the various implementations, which would remove the issue of repeated approval of a trusted source, whether the same contract or a separate one. \n\nGoing this route, there may be less disasters regarding malicious contracts / large ETH losses, as the default  in implementations could be to warn if a signature is non-existent, or not yet marked as a trusted source before execution.\n",
